%N A397204 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} AH(k)/(2*k+1)^4, where AH(k) = A058313(k)/A058312(k) is the k-th alternating harmonic (or skew-harmonic) number.
%H A397204 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.22, p. 426.
%H A397204 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A397204 Equals Pi^3*G/16 + 15*log(2)*zeta(4)/16 - Pi^5/192 - 31*zeta(5)/8 + Pi*polygamma(3, 1/4)/1536, where G is Catalan's constant (A006752), and polygamma(3, 1/4) = psi'''(1/4) is the third derivative of the digamma function at 1/4 (A390074).
%e A397204 0.013699300049135853225210474837981346031785724130521...
%t A397204 RealDigits[Pi^3*Catalan/16 + 15*Log[2]*Zeta[4]/16 - Pi^5/192 - 31*Zeta[5]/8 + Pi*PolyGamma[3, 1/4]/1536, 10, 120, -1][[1]]
%o A397204 (PARI) Pi^3*Catalan/16 + 15*log(2)*zeta(4)/16 - Pi^5/192 - 31*zeta(5)/8 + Pi*psi'''(1/4)/1536
%Y A397204 Cf. A058312, A058313.
%Y A397204 Cf. A002162, A013662, A013663, A006752, A390074.
%Y A397204 Sum_{k>=1} AH(k)/(2*k+1)^m: A397202 (m=2), A397203 (m=3), this constant (m=4).
